The paper discusses the evaluation and enhancement of reactive routing protocols in wireless ad hoc networks, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The use of linear programming models to assess and optimize these protocols also involves mathematical optimization and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the need for energy-efficient and delay reduction techniques, which relates to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The simulations conducted using NS-2 involve system and control theory (cs.SY), and the use of MATLAB for analytical simulations involves machine learning (cs.LG).
